            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef is_palindrome(string):\n    string = string.replace(' ', '').lower()  # Remove spaces, convert to lowercase\n    return string == string[::-1]  # Returns True if palindrome, False otherwise\n# Normalized: 'tom', Reversed: 'mot'\nprint(is_palindrome('tom'))  # Output: False\nprint(is_palindrome('racecar'))  # Output: True\ndef is_palindrome(string):\n    # Using loop to compare characters\n    string = string.replace(' ', '').lower()\n    for i in range(len(string) // 2):\n        if string[i] != string[-(i+1)]:\n            return False\n    return True\nprint(is_palindrome('madam'))  # Output: True\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef is_palindrome(string):\n    result = string == string[::-1]\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef is_palindrome(string):\n    return string == string[::-1]\n\n# Script approach\nstring = 'hello'\nresult = is_palindrome(string)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(is_palindrome('world'))",

