            "initialCode": "def remove_duplicates(input_list):\n    pass\n\ndef remove_duplicates(input_list):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef remove_duplicates(input_list):\n    return list(set(input_list))  # Returns unique elements\ninput_list = [1, 2, 3, 1, 4, 2, 5]\nprint('List with duplicates removed:', remove_duplicates(input_list))  # Output: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\ndef remove_duplicates(input_list):\n    unique_elements = []  # List to store unique elements in order\n    for element in input_list:\n        if element not in unique_elements:\n            unique_elements.append(element)  # Add first occurrence\n    return unique_elements  # Return list with duplicates removed, order preserved\ninput_list = [1, 2, 3, 1, 4, 2, 5]\nprint('List with duplicates removed:', remove_duplicates(input_list))  # Output: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n\n# Alternative solution using dict.fromkeys() to preserve order\ndef remove_duplicates(input_list):\n    return list(dict.fromkeys(input_list))\nprint(remove_duplicates([3, 1, 2, 1, 3]))  # Output: [3, 1, 2]\n\n# Alternative solution using list comprehension with seen set\ndef remove_duplicates(input_list):\n    seen = set()\n    return [x for x in input_list if not (x in seen or seen.add(x))]\nprint(remove_duplicates(['a', 'b', 'a', 'c']))  # Output: ['a', 'b', 'c']\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef remove_duplicates(input_list):\n    result = list(set(input_list))\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef remove_duplicates(input_list):\n    return list(set(input_list))\n\n# Script approach\ninput_list = [3, 7, 2, 9, 1]\nresult = remove_duplicates(input_list)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(remove_duplicates([4, 1, 8, 6, 3]))",

