            "description": "Write a Python function called remove_duplicates_case_insensitive that takes a list of strings as input and returns a new list with duplicate strings removed, ignoring case sensitivity. For example, “hello” and “HELLO” should be considered the same. Do not use set().\n  remove_duplicates(['Hello', 'HELLO', 'world', 'World', 'Python', 'python']) → ['Hello', 'world', 'Python']\n  remove_duplicates(['not', 'not', 'hot', 'HOT', 'cold']) → ['not', 'hot', 'cold']\n  remove_duplicates([]) → []",
            "initialCode": "def remove_duplicates(lst):\n    pass\n\ndef remove_duplicates(lst):\n    pass\n\ndef remove_duplicates(strings):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef remove_duplicates(lst):\n    unique = set()\n    common = []\n    for word in lst:\n        word_lower = word.lower()\n        if word_lower not in unique:\n            common.append(word_lower)\n            unique.add(word_lower)\n    return common\nlst = ['not', 'not', 'hot', 'hot']\nprint(remove_duplicates(lst))\ndef remove_duplicates(lst):\n    unique = set()\n    for word in lst:\n        word_lower = word.lower()\n        if word_lower not in unique:\n            unique.add(word_lower)\n    return unique\nlst = ['not', 'not', 'hot', 'hot', 'cold']\nprint(remove_duplicates(lst))\ndef remove_duplicates(strings):\n    unique_strings = []\n    for string in strings:\n        if string.lower() not in map(str.lower, unique_strings):\n            unique_strings.append(string)\n    return unique_strings\ninput_strings = ['Hello', 'HELLO', 'world', 'World', 'Python', 'python']\nprint('List with case-insensitive duplicates removed:', remove_duplicates(input_strings))\n\n# Alternative solution using dict.fromkeys() with lower()\ndef remove_duplicates(lst):\n    seen = {}\n    for word in lst:\n        lower_word = word.lower()\n        if lower_word not in seen:\n            seen[lower_word] = word\n    return list(seen.values())\nprint(remove_duplicates(['Apple', 'APPLE', 'banana', 'BANANA']))  # Output: ['Apple', 'banana']\n\n# Alternative solution using list comprehension\ndef remove_duplicates(lst):\n    seen = set()\n    return [x for x in lst if x.lower() not in seen and not seen.add(x.lower())]\nprint(remove_duplicates(['Hello', 'HELLO', 'World']))  # Output: ['Hello', 'World']\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef remove_duplicates(lst):\n    return [word_lower for word in lst]\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef remove_duplicates(lst):\n    return list(map(lambda word: word_lower, lst))\n\n# Script approach\nlst = [2, 4, 6, 8]\nresult = remove_duplicates(lst)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(remove_duplicates([1, 3, 5, 7]))",

