            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef max_number():\n    user = input('type 3 numbers: ').split()  # e.g., '10 20 15' \\u2192 ['10', '20', '15']\n    int_number = []  # List to store converted integers\n    for number in user:\n        int_number.append(int(number))  # ['10', '20', '15'] \\u2192 [10, 20, 15]\n    max_num = int_number[0]  # Assume first number is maximum (10)\n    for number in int_number:\n        if number > max_num:  # 20 > 10, so max_num = 20; 15 > 20? No\n            max_num = number  # Update maximum\n    print(max_num)  # Print the maximum number (20)\nmax_number()  # Call the function\n\n# Alternative solution using built-in max()\ndef max_number(a, b, c):\n    return max(a, b, c)\nprint(max_number(10, 25, 15))  # Output: 25\n\n# Alternative solution using ternary operator\ndef max_number(a, b, c):\n    return a if a >= b and a >= c else (b if b >= c else c)\nprint(max_number(100, 50, 75))  # Output: 100\n\n# Alternative solution using sorted()\ndef max_number(numbers):\n    return sorted(numbers)[-1]\nprint(max_number([5, 20, 10]))  # Output: 20\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef max_number():\n    user = input('type 3 numbers: ').split()  # e.g., '10 20 15' \\u2192 ['10', '20', '15']\n    int_number = []  # List to store converted integers\n    for number in user:\n        int_number.append(int(number))  # ['10', '20', '15'] \\u2192 [10, 20, 15]\n    max_num = int_number[0]  # Assume first number is maximum (10)\n    for number in int_number:\n        if number > max_num:  # 20 > 10, so max_num = 20; 15 > 20? No\n            max_num = number  # Update maximum\n    return max_num\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef max_number():\n    user = input('type 3 numbers: ').split()  # e.g., '10 20 15' \\u2192 ['10', '20', '15']\n    int_number = []  # List to store converted integers\n    for number in user:\n        int_number.append(int(number))  # ['10', '20', '15'] \\u2192 [10, 20, 15]\n    max_num = int_number[0]  # Assume first number is maximum (10)\n    for number in int_number:\n        if number > max_num:  # 20 > 10, so max_num = 20; 15 > 20? No\n            max_num = number  # Update maximum\n    result = max_num\n    return result\n\n# Script approach\na = 10\nb = 20\nc = [3, 7, 2, 9, 1]\nresult = max_number(a, b, c)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(max_number(20, 30, [4, 1, 8, 6, 3]))",

