            "initialCode": "def remove_duplicates(elements):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef remove_duplicates(elements):\n    duplicates = []  # List to store unique elements (misleading variable name)\n    for element in elements:\n        if element in duplicates:\n            return duplicates  # Returns partial list with first duplicate found\n        duplicates.append(element)  # Add first occurrence\n    return None  # Returns None if no duplicates found\nlst = ['tree', 'kiss', 'tree']\nprint(remove_duplicates(lst))  # Output: ['tree'] (INCORRECT!)\n\n# Alternative solution using set\ndef remove_duplicates(elements):\n    return list(set(elements))\nprint(remove_duplicates([1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3]))  # Output: [1, 2, 3]\n\n# Alternative solution preserving order\ndef remove_duplicates(elements):\n    seen = set()\n    result = []\n    for item in elements:\n        if item not in seen:\n            seen.add(item)\n            result.append(item)\n    return result\nprint(remove_duplicates([1, 2, 2, 3, 1, 4]))  # Output: [1, 2, 3, 4]\n\n# Alternative solution using dict.fromkeys()\ndef remove_duplicates(elements):\n    return list(dict.fromkeys(elements))\nprint(remove_duplicates(['a', 'b', 'a', 'c']))  # Output: ['a', 'b', 'c']\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef remove_duplicates(elements):\n    return [element for element in elements]\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef remove_duplicates(elements):\n    return list(map(lambda element: element, elements))\n\n# Script approach\nelements = [2, 7, 1, 9]\nresult = remove_duplicates(elements)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(remove_duplicates([5, 3, 8, 4]))",

