            "description": "Write a Python program to check if a number is a prime number. Prompt the user to enter a number.\nExamples:\n  is_prime(2) → True\n  is_prime(17) → True\n  is_prime(1) → False",
            "initialCode": "def is_prime(n):\n    pass\n\ndef main():\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef is_prime(n):\n    if n <= 1:\n        return False  # 1 and negative numbers are not prime\n    if n <= 3:\n        return True  # 2 and 3 are prime numbers\n    if n % 2 == 0 or n % 3 == 0:\n        return False  # Even numbers (except 2) and multiples of 3 are not prime\n    i = 5  # Start from 5 (first number of form 6k-1)\n    while i * i <= n:  # Check up to sqrt(n)\n        if n % i == 0 or n % (i + 2) == 0:\n            return False  # Found a divisor, not prime\n        i += 6  # Move to next pair: 6k+5 and 6k+7\n    return True  # No divisors found, number is prime\ndef main():\n    try:\n        number = int(input('Enter a number: '))  # e.g., 17\n        if is_prime(number):\n            print(f'{number} is a prime number.')  # Display success message\n        else:\n            print(f'{number} is not a prime number.')  # Display failure message\n    except ValueError:\n        print('Please enter a valid integer.')  # Error message\nmain()  # Call the main function\n\n# Alternative simple solution\ndef is_prime(n):\n    if n < 2:\n        return False\n    for i in range(2, int(n ** 0.5) + 1):\n        if n % i == 0:\n            return False\n    return True\nprint(is_prime(17))  # Output: True\nprint(is_prime(10))  # Output: False\nprint(is_prime(2))   # Output: True\n\n# Alternative solution using all()\ndef is_prime(n):\n    if n < 2:\n        return False\n    return all(n % i != 0 for i in range(2, int(n ** 0.5) + 1))\nprint(is_prime(23))  # Output: True\nprint(is_prime(15))  # Output: False\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef is_prime(n):\n    result = False\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef is_prime(n):\n    return False\n\n# Script approach\nn = 6\nresult = is_prime(n)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(is_prime(15))",

