            "initialCode": "def gcd(a, b):\n    pass\n\ndef main():\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef gcd(a, b):\n    while b != 0:\n        a, b = b, a % b  # Tuple unpacking: assigns b to a, and a % b to b simultaneously\n    return a\ndef main():\n    num1 = int(input('Enter the first number: '))\n    num2 = int(input('Enter the second number: '))\n    result = gcd(num1, num2)\n    print(f'The GCD of {num1} and {num2} is: {result}')\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n\n# Alternative solution using math.gcd\ndef gcd(a, b):\n    import math\n    return math.gcd(a, b)\nprint(gcd(48, 18))  # Output: 6\nprint(gcd(100, 75))  # Output: 25\n\n# Alternative solution using recursion\ndef gcd(a, b):\n    if b == 0:\n        return a\n    return gcd(b, a % b)\nprint(gcd(56, 98))  # Output: 14\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef gcd(a, b):\n    result = a\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef gcd(a, b):\n    return a\n\n# Script approach\na = 10\nb = 20\nresult = gcd(a, b)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(gcd(20, 30))",

