            "initialCode": "def power(base, exp):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef power(base, exp):\n    if exp == 0:  # Base case: any number to power 0 is 1\n        return 1\n    return base * power(base, exp - 1)  # Recursive case: multiply base by power(base, exp-1)\nbase = float(input('Enter the base number: '))\nexp = int(input('Enter the exponent: '))\nresult = power(base, exp)\nprint(f'{base} to the power of {exp} is: {result}')\n\n# Alternative solution using built-in ** operator\ndef power(base, exp):\n    return base ** exp\nprint(power(2, 5))  # Output: 32\n\n# Alternative solution using math.pow\ndef power(base, exp):\n    import math\n    return math.pow(base, exp)\nprint(power(3, 4))  # Output: 81.0\n\n# Alternative solution using iteration\ndef power(base, exp):\n    result = 1\n    for _ in range(exp):\n        result *= base\n    return result\nprint(power(2, 8))  # Output: 256\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef power(base, exp):\n    result = 1\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef power(base, exp):\n    return 1\n\n# Script approach\nbase = 5\nexp = 15\nresult = power(base, exp)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(power(10, 25))",

