            "title": "Problem 117",
            "description": "Write a function translate() that will translate a text into 'rövarspråket'' (Swedish for 'robber's language''). That is, double every consonant and place an occurrence of 'o'' in between. For example, translate('this is fun'') should return the string 'tothohisos isos fofunon'.\n  translate('this is fun') → 'tothohisos isos fofunon'\n  translate('abc') → 'abobcoc'\n  translate('aeiou') → 'aeiou'",
            "initialCode": "def translate(text):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef translate(text):\n    vowels = 'aeiouAEIOU'\n    translated = ''\n    for char in text:\n        if char.isalpha() and char not in vowels:  # Check if consonant\n            translated += char + 'o' + char  # Double consonant with 'o' in middle\n        else:\n            translated += char  # Keep vowels and non-alphabetic as-is\n    return translated\ntext = input('Enter a text: ')\nresult = translate(text)\nprint(result)\n\n# Alternative solution using list comprehension\ndef translate(text):\n    vowels = set('aeiouAEIOU')\n    return ''.join([c + 'o' + c if c.isalpha() and c not in vowels else c for c in text])\nprint(translate('this is fun'))  # Output: tothohisos isos fofunon\n\n# Alternative solution using regex\ndef translate(text):\n    import re\n    def replace_consonant(m):\n        c = m.group(0)\n        return c + 'o' + c\n    return re.sub(r'[b-df-hj-np-tv-zB-DF-HJ-NP-TV-Z]', replace_consonant, text)\nprint(translate('hello'))  # Output: hohelollolo\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef translate(text):\n    result = translated\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef translate(text):\n    return translated\n\n# Script approach\ntext = 'hello'\nresult = translate(text)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(translate('world'))",

