            "initialCode": "def reverse(string):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef reverse(string):\n    reversed_string = ''\n    for char in string:\n        reversed_string = char + reversed_string  # Prepend char (builds from right to left)\n    return reversed_string\nstring = input('Enter a string: ')\nresult = reverse(string)\nprint(result)\n\n# Alternative solution using slicing\ndef reverse(string):\n    return string[::-1]\nprint(reverse('I am testing'))  # Output: gnitset ma I\n\n# Alternative solution using reversed and join\ndef reverse(string):\n    return ''.join(reversed(string))\nprint(reverse('hello'))  # Output: olleh\n\n# Alternative solution using recursion\ndef reverse(string):\n    if len(string) <= 1:\n        return string\n    return reverse(string[1:]) + string[0]\nprint(reverse('python'))  # Output: nohtyp\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef reverse(string):\n    result = reversed_string\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef reverse(string):\n    return reversed_string\n\n# Script approach\nstring = 'hello'\nresult = reverse(string)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(reverse('world'))",

