            "initialCode": "def palindromes(string):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef palindromes(string):\n    for char in string:  # Loop doesn't use char variable\n        if string == string[::-1]:  # Compares string with reverse (same check every iteration)\n            return True\n    return False\nstring = 'radarh'\nprint(palindromes(string))\n\n# Alternative solution using slicing\ndef is_palindrome(string):\n    return string == string[::-1]\nprint(is_palindrome('radar'))  # Output: True\nprint(is_palindrome('hello'))  # Output: False\n\n# Alternative solution using two pointers\ndef is_palindrome(string):\n    left, right = 0, len(string) - 1\n    while left < right:\n        if string[left] != string[right]:\n            return False\n        left += 1\n        right -= 1\n    return True\nprint(is_palindrome('level'))  # Output: True\n\n# Alternative solution using all()\ndef is_palindrome(string):\n    return all(string[i] == string[-(i+1)] for i in range(len(string)//2))\nprint(is_palindrome('madam'))  # Output: True\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef palindromes(string):\n    result = True\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef palindromes(string):\n    return True\n\n# Script approach\nstring = 'hello'\nresult = palindromes(string)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(palindromes('world'))",

