            "description": "Write a function invert_dictionary that takes a dictionary as input and returns a new dictionary where the keys are the values from the input dictionary, and the values are lists of keys from the input dictionary that had that value.\nExamples:\n  invert_dictionary({'x': 10, 'y': 20, 'z': 10}) → {10: ['x', 'z'], 20: ['y']}\n  invert_dictionary({'a': 1, 'b': 2, 'c': 1}) → {1: ['a', 'c'], 2: ['b']}",
            "initialCode": "def invert_dictionary(input_dict):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef invert_dictionary(input_dict):\n    inverted = {}  # New dictionary for inverted structure\n    for key, value in input_dict.items():\n        if value not in inverted:\n            inverted[value] = []\n        inverted[value].append(key)  # Add key to list of keys that had this value\n    return inverted\ninput_dict = {'a': 1, 'b': 2, 'c': 1}  # 'a' and 'c' both have value 1\nresult = invert_dictionary(input_dict)  # Result: {1: ['a', 'c'], 2: ['b']}\nprint(result)\n\n# Alternative solution using collections.defaultdict\ndef invert_dictionary(input_dict):\n    from collections import defaultdict\n    inverted = defaultdict(list)\n    for key, value in input_dict.items():\n        inverted[value].append(key)\n    return dict(inverted)\nprint(invert_dictionary({'a': 1, 'b': 2, 'c': 1}))\n\n# Alternative solution using dict.setdefault\ndef invert_dictionary(input_dict):\n    inverted = {}\n    for key, value in input_dict.items():\n        inverted.setdefault(value, []).append(key)\n    return inverted\nprint(invert_dictionary({'x': 10, 'y': 20, 'z': 10}))  # Output: {10: ['x', 'z'], 20: ['y']}\n\n# Alternative solution using dictionary comprehension\ndef invert_dictionary(input_dict):\n    return {v: [k for k in input_dict if input_dict[k] == v] for v in set(input_dict.values())}\nprint(invert_dictionary({'a': 1, 'b': 2, 'c': 1}))  # Output: {1: ['a', 'c'], 2: ['b']}\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef invert_dictionary(input_dict):\n    result = inverted\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef invert_dictionary(input_dict):\n    return inverted\n\n# Script approach\ninput_dict = {'a': 1, 'b': 2}\nresult = invert_dictionary(input_dict)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(invert_dictionary({'x': 10, 'y': 20}))",

