            "initialCode": "def reverse_number(n):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef reverse_number(n):\n    reversed_num = 0\n    while n > 0:\n        reversed_num = reversed_num * 10 + n % 10  # Append last digit of n to reversed_num\n        n = n // 10  # Remove last digit: 123\\u219212\\u21921\\u21920\n    return reversed_num  # Returns reversed number: 12345 \\u2192 54321\nnum = int(input('Enter a number: '))\nprint('Reversed number:', reverse_number(num))\n\n# Alternative using string slicing\ndef reverse_number(n):\n    sign = -1 if n < 0 else 1\n    return sign * int(str(abs(n))[::-1])\nprint(reverse_number(12345))\n\n# Alternative using for loop\ndef reverse_number(n):\n    sign = -1 if n < 0 else 1\n    n = abs(n)\n    rev = 0\n    for d in str(n):\n        rev = rev * 10 + int(d)\n    return rev * sign\nprint(reverse_number(12345))\n\n# Alternative using list reversal\ndef reverse_number(n):\n    sign = -1 if n < 0 else 1\n    return sign * int(''.join(reversed(str(abs(n)))))\nprint(reverse_number(12345))\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef reverse_number(n):\n    result = reversed_num\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef reverse_number(n):\n    return reversed_num\n\n# Script approach\nn = 6\nresult = reverse_number(n)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(reverse_number(15))",

