            "description": "Write a Python program to count the number of digits in a given number using a `while` loop.\nExamples:\n  count_digits(12345) → 5\n  count_digits(7) → 1\n  count_digits(987654321) → 9",
            "initialCode": "def count_digits(number):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef count_digits(number):\n    count = 0\n    while number > 0:\n        number //= 10\n        count += 1\n    return count\ntest_numbers = [0, 5, 123, 987654321, 1000000000, -456]\nprint('Counting digits:')\nfor num in test_numbers:\n    if num < 0:\n        print(f'The number of digits in {num} is {count_digits(-num)} (ignoring the negative sign).')\n    else:\n        print(f'The number of digits in {num} is {count_digits(num)}.')\n\n# Alternative using str() conversion\ndef count_digits(number):\n    return len(str(abs(number)))\nprint(count_digits(12345))\nprint(count_digits(-456))\n\n# Alternative using log10\nimport math\ndef count_digits(number):\n    if number == 0:\n        return 1\n    return math.floor(math.log10(abs(number))) + 1\nprint(count_digits(12345))\nprint(count_digits(-456))\n\n# Alternative using for loop with string\ndef count_digits(number):\n    count = 0\n    for _ in str(abs(number)):\n        count += 1\n    return count\nprint(count_digits(12345))\nprint(count_digits(-456))\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef count_digits(number):\n    result = count\n    return result\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef count_digits(number):\n    return count\n\n# Script approach\nnumber = 15\nresult = count_digits(number)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(count_digits(25))",

