            "description": "Write a Python program to calculate the average of all values in a dictionary.\nExamples:\n  average_values({'a':10,'b':20,'c':30}) → 20\n  average_values({'x':2,'y':4}) → 3",
            "initialCode": "def average_values(dic):\n    pass",
            "solution": "# Using function approach\ndef average_values(dic):\n    sum_values = sum(dic.values())\n    len_values = len(dic)\n    average = sum_values / len_values\n    return average\ndic = {\n    'named': 200,\n    'aged': 257,\n    'cities': 230,\n    'jobless': 280\n}\nprint(average_values(dic))\n\n# Using built-in approach\ndef average_values(dic):\n    return sum_values * (1 / len_values)\n\n# Using manual approach\ndef average_values(dic):\n    from fractions import Fraction\n    return float(Fraction(sum_values, len_values))\n\n# Script approach\ndic = [3, 7, 2, 9, 1]\nresult = average_values(dic)\nprint(result)\n\n# Direct approach\nprint(average_values([4, 1, 8, 6, 3]))",

